100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 11, 1925, the world witnessed significant political shifts as the League of Nations convened to address ongoing disputes in the Middle East and Europe, aiming to promote peace and stability. In Italy, Mussolini's government continued to consolidate power, stifling dissent and tightening its grip on the nation. Meanwhile, in the United States, the rise of Prohibition sparked heated debates over morality and law enforcement, with increasing calls for repeal.
